profile_positions.description:
Accountable for oversight, leadership and management of the HECOR Biostatistics team that is responsible for providing statistical expertise for economic, epidemiology and clinical outcomes projects across ASMA therapeutic areas. I manage the group of Statistical Programmers and Clinical Biostatisticians and lead large and complex projects, interact with cross functional teams, and am accountable for the statistical soundness of all project plans, output and deliverables for the assigned projects. As the Director I: 

•	ensure that health economic and clinical outcomes projects are statisically valid and appropriately planned, resourced and executed;  
•	lead and prioritize multiple concomitant HECOR projects, including but not limited to, data generation in health economic, comparative effectiveness, real world data, patient reported outcomes, disease state and epidemiologic initiatives across therapeutic areas;
•	establish effective communication with all internal stakeholders to understand and support the HECOR statistical needs of the business; and
•	manage collaborations and lead statistical analysis across multiple external database vendors and experts to ensure that Astellas sponsored HECOR initiatives are clinically relevant and support the needs of patients, health care providers and payers.
